LITTLE MUSIC leaned out and bobbled very slightly at the start, pressed the leader from the three path, bid at the five sixteenths pole, vied turning for home, but was outkicked by an outer rival entering midstretch and edged place. SUMMER DANCE leaned in a touch at the start, set the pace inside of a prompting foe while a path off of the rail around the turn, resisted that foe's challenge turning for home, but got headed by another outer bidder in midstretch and yielded late. MISSY BEE lacked speed in the two path and got outrun. TONIC AND GIN tracked in the four path and weakened nearing the lane. ROSE DARLING broke slowly, lagged behind around the turn and cut the gap on weakening rivals late.

CRUSADING was rowdy in the post parade, then leaned in at the start before exchanging early contact with an inner rival in the opening stages, laid off of the pace two wide and between horses, then lacked a bid while one paced.
